item.title: Rep. Andy Harris Elected Freedom Caucus Chair
item.description: The House Freedom Caucus elected Rep. Andy Harris, R-Md., as its new chair Tuesday.He replaces Rep. Bob Good, R-Va., who lost his June primary and will leave office early next year. Good, whose term as chair was supposed to run through December 2025, announced last week he...

item.title: Hillary Clinton, Who Spread Election Propaganda for Years, Wants to Jail Americans for Misinformation
Russo-Chinese Arctic war games spur US response as Alaska officials warn only strength can deter crisis
item.description: The Army deployed about 130 airborne members to Shemya Island on the far end of the Aleutian chain in response to aggression from Russia and China this week.

item.title: Fleitz to Newsmax: Beepers Likely Easier Than Phones for Explosives
item.description: Warfare where beepers could explode is much more likely than a cell phone being caused to blow up, Fred Fleitz told Newsmax on Tuesday, regarding pagers used by hundreds of Hezbollah members almost simultaneously exploding in Lebanon and Syria.

item.title: NEW: Man Who Tried to Assassinate Trump Was Flagged by a Second Federal Agency, Then Ignored
DOJ's new voter-roll guidance quietly issued; critic warns it may 'intimidate' election workers
item.description: Former DOJ attorney Gene Hamilton says the Biden-Harris DOJ's new guidelines on voter list maintenance are intended to intimidate state and local election officials.

item.title: Rep. Fallon to Newsmax: Biden Can Grant Trump Full SS Protection
item.description: Rep. Pat Fallon, R-Texas, stressed that the executive branch holds the authority to provide former President Donald Trump with comprehensive Secret Service protection following two recent assassination attempts.

item.title: WATCH: JD Vance Puts on Master Class in Schooling New York Times Reporter Over the Springfield Question
Vulnerable Dem senator who touts record 'fighting' lobbyists has long history of hiring them
item.description: Ohio Democratic. Sen. Sherrod Brown was ranked as one of the top senators for hiring lobbyists after years of lamenting the influencing of lobbying in Congress.

item.title: Trump to Visit Landmark in Pa. With Polish President
item.description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump is scheduled to visit The National Shrine of Our Lady of Czestochowa in Bucks County, Pennsylvania, this weekend alongside Polish President Andrzej Duda.

item.title: No Tax on Tips Bill Introduced in Congress - By a Democrat
House GOP braces for government funding chaos as Republican rebels mutiny before vote
item.description: Tensions are running high again within the House GOP as Speaker Mike Johnson pushes ahead with a vote on his government funding plan that some Republicans oppose.

item.title: Ohio AG Yost to Newsmax: Feds, Not State, Responsible for Haitian Crisis
item.description: The crisis caused by an influx of 20,000 Haitian migrants into Springfield, Ohio, is giving Americans an education on the detrimental effects of the Biden administration's open-border policies, Republican Ohio Attorney General Dave Yost told Newsmax on Tuesday.
